cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the security analysis of the OAuth 2.0 protocol, which is a crucial aspect of computer security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves formal modeling and analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). The OAuth 2.0 protocol is widely used in web applications, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper proposes fixes for identified vulnerabilities, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
